# Botium Toys Controls and Compliance Checklist

## üîê Controls Assessment

| Control | In Place? | Explanation |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| Least Privilege | ‚ùå No | There is no least privilege. Every employee has access to all data, including PII and SPII. |
| Disaster Recovery Plans | ‚ùå No | No disaster recovery plans are in place. No backups exist. Business continuity is at risk. |
| Password Policies | ‚ùå No | Password requirements are minimal and don‚Äôt meet complexity standards. Risk of unauthorized access. |
| Separation of Duties | ‚ùå No | The CEO manages payroll and day-to-day operations. This increases fraud risk. |
| Firewall | ‚úÖ Yes | A firewall is in place with defined security rules. |
| Intrusion Detection System (IDS) | ‚ùå No | No IDS is used. The IT department needs this capability. |
| Backups | ‚ùå No | No backups of critical data exist. High risk to business continuity. |
| Antivirus Software | ‚úÖ Yes | Antivirus is installed and monitored regularly. |
| Legacy System Monitoring | ‚ö†Ô∏è Partial | Legacy systems are monitored, but irregularly and without clear procedures. |
| Encryption | ‚ùå No | No encryption is implemented. Confidentiality is compromised. |
| Password Management System | ‚ùå No | No password manager. IT cannot efficiently support lockouts or recovery. |
| Physical Locks | ‚úÖ Yes | Sufficient locks exist at physical locations. |
| CCTV Surveillance | ‚úÖ Yes | CCTV is installed and functioning. |
| Fire Detection/Prevention | ‚úÖ Yes | Fire alarms and sprinklers are present. |

