## ‚úÖ Compliance Checklist

### PCI DSS

| Best Practice | In Place? | Explanation |
|---------------|-----------|-------------|
| Restrict access to credit card info | ‚ùå No | All employees have access to internal data. |
| Secure credit card storage and transmission | ‚ùå No | Credit card data is not encrypted. |
| Implement encryption for financial data | ‚ùå No | No encryption currently in use. |
| Use secure password policies | ‚ùå No | No password management system; policies are weak. |

### GDPR

| Best Practice | In Place? | Explanation |
|---------------|-----------|-------------|
| Secure E.U. customer data | ‚ùå No | No encryption is in place. |
| Notify customers within 72 hours of breach | ‚úÖ Yes | A response plan exists. |
| Classify and inventory data | ‚ö†Ô∏è Partial | Data is inventoried but not classified. |
| Enforce privacy policies and processes | ‚úÖ Yes | Enforced among IT and staff. |

### SOC (Type 1 & 2)

| Best Practice | In Place? | Explanation |
|---------------|-----------|-------------|
| User access policies | ‚ùå No | All employees have access. Least Privilege is not in place. |
| Confidentiality of PII/SPII | ‚ùå No | No encryption or protection of sensitive data. |
| Data integrity | ‚úÖ Yes | Data is consistent and validated. |
| Controlled data availability | ‚ùå No | All data is openly accessible. Should be restricted. |

---

## üí° Recommendations

To improve Botium Toys‚Äô security posture:

- Implement **Least Privilege** and **Separation of Duties**
- Enforce strong **password policies** and adopt a **password manager**
- Add **encryption** for sensitive data
- Use an **Intrusion Detection System (IDS)**
- Develop a **disaster recovery plan** and ensure regular **backups**
- **Classify assets** for improved data handling and protection
